"active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Ours is not an empty file issue. However, the code section emanating the exception is same.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ashahab","name":"ashahab","key":"ashahab","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562"},"displayName":"Abin Shahab","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2013-08-06T22:46:14.183+0000","updated":"2013-08-06T22:46:14.183+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12662238/comment/13733660","id":"13733660","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ashahab","name":"ashahab","key":"ashahab","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562"},"displayName":"Abin Shahab","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Root cause of this issue is Not picking the YarnRunner as the job runner when hive.exec.mode.local.auto=true\nmapreduce.framework.name gets set to 'local' instead of 'yarn'. This results in the LocalJobRunner being used as the JobRunner, and messes up the path creation. ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ashahab","name":"ashahab","key":"ashahab","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562"},"displayName":"Abin Shahab","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2013-08-08T16:39:23.687+0000","updated":"2013-08-08T16:39:23.687+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12662238/comment/13741219","id":"13741219","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ashahab","name":"ashahab","key":"ashahab","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562"},"displayName":"Abin Shahab","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Root cause of this issue is:\nThe classpath for jars in local mode points to a real file on disk. However, the JobSubmitter was cutting off the protocol part of the path. By default DistributedCache assumes that a protocol-less file is from HDFS, and that was causing the FileNotFound exception.\nThe solution is to the entire path to the DistributedCache, which allowed DistributedCache to find it in the file system.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ashahab","name":"ashahab","key":"ashahab","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=ashahab&avatarId=18562","16x16":"https://issues.apach